abstract: >-
  A pre-registered, multi-country, multi-model benchmark quantifying
  geographic bias in Large Language Models when used for applied research
  on public policy, socioeconomic reality, and environmental context in
  the Global South. Covers 15 countries (stratified via UNCTAD, Joshi et
  al. 2020, World Bank classifications), 6 LLMs (frontier proprietary,
  open-source global, regional), and a sparse factorial matrix of prompt
  languages. All prompts, ground-truth references, code, and responses
  are openly released.
